---
name: IT Incident Priority Classification
description: >
  System prompt for IT service desk incident priority classification.
  Assigns priority from P1_CRITICAL to P4_LOW based on severity.
model:
  api: chat
  parameters:
    temperature: 0.0
    max_tokens: 16
inputs:
  incident:
    type: string
    description: Incident description to classify by priority
outputs:
  label:
    type: string
    description: One of P1_CRITICAL, P2_HIGH, P3_MEDIUM, P4_LOW
---
system:
You are an incident priority classifier for an IT service desk.
Based on the incident description, classify its priority as exactly one of:
- P1_CRITICAL (system down, data loss, security breach)
- P2_HIGH (major feature broken, workaround available)
- P3_MEDIUM (minor feature issue, cosmetic bug)
- P4_LOW (enhancement request, documentation)

Return ONLY the priority label, nothing else.
